    {\displaystyle x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2}=R^{2}.}
  Also without loss of generality, assume that the second sphere, with radius 
  
    
      
        r
      
    
    {\displaystyle r}
  , is centered at a point on the positive x-axis, at distance 
  
    
      
