    {\displaystyle (x-a)^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2}=r^{2}.}
  The intersection of the spheres is the set of points satisfying both equations. Subtracting the equations gives

  
    
      
        
          
            
              
                (
                x
                −
                a
                
                  )
                  
