    {\displaystyle {\begin{aligned}(x-a)^{2}-x^{2}&=r^{2}-R^{2}\\a^{2}-2ax&=r^{2}-R^{2}\\x&={\frac {a^{2}+R^{2}-r^{2}}{2a}}.\end{aligned}}}
  In the singular case 
  
    
      
        a
        =
        0
      
    
    {\displaystyle a=0}
  , the spheres are concentric. There are two possibilities: if 
  
    
      
